<paragraph id="215A368EEB458B034CA44204FCEDFD50" blockId="2.[136,1452,320,666]" pageId="2" pageNumber="296">
Since all names are considered invalid names (the Shenzhen Code, article 39.1), they cannot be used, and should be considered as excluded names. As mentioned above, according to the original descriptions made by Tīcs, all his names have been unambiguously attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="E6E54D0DEB458B034CFA42BCFEEDFD53" authorityName="Lindl. ex Spach" authorityYear="1834" baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1780" box="[214,326,644,665]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Chaenomeles" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="2" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="1391EA9CEB458B034CFA42BCFEEDFD53" box="[214,326,644,665]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="296">C. japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All cultivar denominations also apply to this species
</paragraph>
